tourBios.carHigh:
2005: Played his first full Champions Tour season, making 23 starts. Top finish was a T10 at the Turtle Bay Championship along Oahu's North Shore...Added a second T10 six weeks later, at the SBC Classic in California.

2001: Made the cut in 11 of 23 tournaments on the Web.com Tour. Finished No. 53 on the final money list with $88,733...Posted three top-10s and six top-25s...Finished T3 at the Ozarks Open and the Shreveport Open...Finished T6 at the Gila River Classic after rounds of 67-67-64-69...Finished T17 at the Tour Championship in October.

2000: Made the cut in 18 of 27 Web.com Tour events, with four top-10 and 12 top-25 finishes...His best outing of the season came in the third event on the schedule, the Mississippi Gulf Coast Open.

1999: Opened the season by making the cut in four straight events, including a T5 at the Florida Classic, where he carded a final-round 6-under-par 65...Tied for seventh at the Upstate Classic...Was also T10 at the Oregon Classic.

1994: Earned his playing privileges again by finishing T10 at the PGA TOUR's Qualifying Tournament. 

1993: Was T32 at the PGA TOUR's Qualifying Tournament.

1989: Had his best PGA TOUR finish, a T5 at the Hawaiian Open.

1988: Finished third at the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament.

1986: Successfully defended his Metropolitan PGA Championship.

1985: Winner of the National PGA Match Play Championship.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Earned All-American honors in 1976 and 1977 at Troy State University.
tourBios.personal: Was a college standout at Troy State University in Alabama, where he was a two-time All-American. Led Troy to a pair of national titles in 1976 and 1977.

tourBios.exmtStatus: T4 at 2004 Champions Tour National Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.otherVics: (8): 1985 National PGA Match Play Championship. 1985 Metropolitan PGA Championship. 1986 Metropolitan PGA Championship. 2003 The Patriot [Sunbelt]. 2004 The Patriot [Sunbelt], North Carolina Senior Open [Sunbelt], Woodbridge Senior Championship [Sunbelt], Darby Bank/Savannah Senior Open [Sunbelt].
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Member of the Nationwide Tour in 1990-94 and 1997-2001...PGA TOUR member in 1982, 1989, 1994-95...Made 115 starts in his PGA TOUR career and made 35 cuts, while his Nationwide Tour ledger includes 243 starts, with 130 cuts...Best finish of his PGA TOUR career was a T5 at the 1989 Hawaiian Open, and it helped him to season earnings of $60,838, his best ever on that Tour...Won one title on the Nationwide Tour, the 1991 Lake City Classic...Enjoyed his best season from an earnings standpoint in 2000 when he won $132,426 and finished 35th on the Nationwide Tour money list. Winner of the 1985 National PGA Match Play Championship...Was the 1985 and 1986 Metropolitan PGA Champion...Finished third at the 1988 PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament.
tourBios.personal: Was a college standout at Troy State University in Alabama, where he was a two-time All-American. Led Troy to a pair of national titles in 1976 and 1977.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was 1st in 1991 at the Ben Hogan Lake City Classic.
